Install Maven:

1. Download Maven from: https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi
2. Download the apache-maven-3.x.y-bin.zip file and extract
3. Set the path to the bin folder from maven in the PATH system variable
4. Run mvn --version to check if everything installed correctly

Install Git:

1. Download Git from home page: https://git-scm.com/downloads
2. Use the installer and click Next until the end :)
3. Clone a project using git command: "git cline <https:// path>"

Install IntelliJ:

1. Download from IntelliJ website: https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/download/#section=windows
2. Use the installer and click Next until the end
3. Create a new Maven project in IntelliJ in order to use Maven...also the pom file should be edited with the appropriate dependencies
4. This is an example of a depedency:

 <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>

 <artifactId>selenium-chrome-driver</artifactId>

 <version>3.11.0</version>




Add Chrome Driver:

1. Download the Chrome driver/ gekodriver from the SeleniumHQ pageand drag and drop it in IntelliJ over the project
OR Add the Path to the folder where Chrome Driver is located in System Variables so all projects will use it from there from now on. :)